{
  "script": "Purpose isn't a destination we find on a map. It's the quiet friction between who you are and the work you can't leave alone. It lives in the dirt, the repetition, and the small, stubborn choices that define your pulse. Stop looking for a sign. Just look at your hands. Purpose is not a place you arrive. It's is the map you draw with every step.",
